©The Ferryman‚Äôs Seat

The Ferryman‚Äôs seat, located on the previous building at this site, was constructed for the convenience of Bankside
watermen, who operated ferrying services across the river.
The seat‚Äôs age is unknown, but it is thought to have ancient origins.

